Welcome back to #UNGA, @bts.bighitofficial 💜⁣
⁣
#FlashbackFriday © UNICEF/UN0238385/Garten, UN Photo

1.8 trillion ‒ and counting.
 
That’s the number of in-class hours that schoolchildren around the world have lost due to the COVID-19 pandemic. They cannot wait any longer.
 
The ‘No Time to Lose’ installation at the United Nations in New York is a stark reminder of the price children are paying for the global education crisis. Our message to world leaders? #ReopenSchools as soon as possible and protect the future of an entire generation.

© UNICEF/UN0522076/Gary He/UNICEF via Getty Images

The pandemic has taken away so much from so many. For nearly 77 million children, it has taken away their classrooms for the past 18 months.⁣
⁣
We're closing down our channels for the next 18 hours to send one message to the world: #ReopenSchools as soon as possible.⁣
⁣
We’ll be back tomorrow. When will they be back in school?
